  <name>Linux Hardware Database</name>
  <summary>Privacy-first Linux hardware compatibility database</summary>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      Linux Hardware Database is a community-driven tool that helps Linux users ensure optimal hardware compatibility 
      through privacy-preserving hardware detection, automated configuration recommendations, and transparent 
      community-driven validation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Key features:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Privacy-preserving hardware detection using multiple detection tools</li>
      <li>Automated configuration recommendations for detected hardware</li>
      <li>Community-driven compatibility database with GitHub integration</li>
      <li>Support for multiple output formats (JSON, YAML, Markdown)</li>
      <li>Shell completions for bash, zsh, and fish</li>
      <li>Cross-platform support with native GUI interface</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The application uses advanced privacy techniques including cryptographic anonymization with HMAC-SHA256, 
      differential privacy with calibrated noise injection, and k-anonymity principles to protect user privacy 
      while maintaining statistical utility for hardware compatibility analysis.
    </p>
  </description>
  
